https://github.com/mitmproxy/mitmproxy/pull/6454 has a fix, release should be out in an hour or so. Thanks for bearing with us. :)

What do I have to do to read WebSocket stuff though? @mhils 

can mitmweb be used for the UDP and TCP and TLS stuff?
@karl-police: mitmweb does support WebSockets, as well a raw TCP and UDP. Depends a bit on the proxy mode what you are getting.
